ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Miscellaneous comments on study, interview, methodology relevant to this form data
Regarding techniques of disciplining, I feel I have learned
Notes: 1 = nothing; 2 = very little; 3 = a few techniques; 4 = several useful techniques; 5 = very many useful techniques

ElementDescription: Regarding techniques for teaching my child new skills, I feel I have learned
Notes: 1 = nothing; 2 = very little; 3 = a few techniques; 4 = several useful techniques; 5 = very many useful techniques

ElementDescription: Regarding the relationship between myself and my child, I feel we get along
Notes: 1 = much worse than before; 2 = somewhat worse than before; 3 = the same as before; 4 = somewhat better than before; 5 = very much better than before

ElementDescription: Regarding my confidence in my ability to discipline my child, I feel
Notes: 1 = much less confiedent; 2 = somewhat less confident; 3 = the same; 4 = somewhat more confident; 5 = much more confident

ElementDescription: The major behavior problems that my child presented at home before the program started are at this time
Notes: 1 = considerably worse; 2 = somewhat worse; 3 = the same; 4 = somewhat improved; 5 = greatly improved

ElementDescription: I feel that my child's compliance to my commands or requests is at this time
Notes: 1 = considerably worse; 2 = somewhat worse; 3 = the same; 4 = somewhat improved; 5 = greatly improved

ElementDescription: Regarding the progress my child has made in his/her general behavior, I am
Notes: 1 = very  dissatisfied; 2 = somewhat  dissatisfied; 3 = neutral; 4 = somewhat satisfied;  5 = very satisfied

ElementDescription: To what degree has the treatment program helped with other general personal or family problems not directly related to your child in the program?
Notes: 1 = hindered much more than helped; 2 = hindered slightly; 3 = neither helped nor hindered; 4 = helped somewhat; 5 = helped very much

ElementDescription: I feel the type of program that was used to help me improve the behaviors of my child was
Notes: 1 = very poor; 2 = poor; 3 = adequate; 4 = good; 5 = very good

ElementDescription: My general feeling about the program I participated in, is
Notes: 1 = I disliked it very much; 2 = I disliked it somewhat; 3. I feel neutral; 4 = I liked it somewhat; 5 = I liked it very much

ElementDescription: Level of comfort with the ethnicity of your therapist/coach
Notes: 1= not comfortable; 2= somewhat uncomfortable; 3= neutral; 4= somewhat comfortable; 5= very comfortable

ElementDescription: Level of comfort with the ethnicity of the assessment staff
Notes: 1= not comfortable; 2= somewhat uncomfortable; 3= neutral; 4= somewhat comfortable; 5= very comfortable

ElementDescription: To what degree have the skills you learned in this treatment program been accepted by the people in your family? (e.g., mother/father, adult siblings, other extended relatives)
Notes: 1= not accepted; 2= somewhat not accepted; 3= neutral, 4= somewhat accepted; 5= very accepted

ElementDescription: To what degree have the skills you learned in this treatment program been accepted by the people in your community? (neighbors, other school/Head Start parent, friends)
Notes: 1= not accepted; 2= somewhat not accepted; 3= neutral, 4= somewhat accepted; 5= very accepted

ElementDescription: To what degree do you feel the skills you have learned in this program are consistent with your religious or spiritual upbringing and values?
Notes: 1= not consistent; 2= somewhat inconsistent; 3= neutral; 4= somewhat consistent; 5= Very consistent

ElementDescription: Therapy Attitude Inventory total score
